## Pattern Detection (Consistency Check)

Runs automatically **after scoring**, only when the employee has **4 or more prior scored reports** on the same goal. A second Gemini call compares the current report against the previous 4.

### Patterns detected

| Flag | What it means |
|------|--------------|
| `ESCALATING_CLAIMS` | Contribution language inflates week-over-week ("helped" → "led" → "drove" → "owned") but AI scores stay flat or decline |
| `STAGNANT_LANGUAGE` | Same sentence patterns, same claim types, same phrasing across reports — employee is templating rather than reflecting actual work |
| `STABLE` | No concerning pattern detected |

Result saved as `consistency_flag` + `consistency_note` on the `reports` row.

---

## Score Calculation

```
goalAvg   = average of all criteria scores (weighted by criterion.weight)
orgAvg    = average of org metric scores
goalWeight = org setting (default 70)
orgWeight  = 100 - goalWeight

finalScore = (goalAvg × goalWeight%) + (orgAvg × orgWeight%)
```

If no org metrics are configured, `finalScore = goalAvg` (goal criteria carry 100%).

