## AI Output Structure (per report)

```json
{
  "overall_score": 7.4,
  "overall_confidence": "medium",
  "overall_reasoning": "2–4 sentence holistic verdict",
  "integrity_flags": [],
  "criteria_scores": [
    {
      "name": "Criterion Name",
      "weight": 40,
      "score": 7.0,
      "confidence": "medium",
      "evidence": "Direct quote or reference from report",
      "reasoning": "What was demonstrated vs target vs historical trend",
      "coaching_note": "Actionable manager advice if score < 7.0, else null"
    }
  ],
  "org_metrics": [
    {
      "name": "Metric Name",
      "score": 6.5,
      "reasoning": "1–2 sentences"
    }
  ]
}
```

`coaching_note` applies only to goal criteria (never org_metrics). It is `null` for scores ≥ 7.0. For scores below 7.0 it must be one concrete, specific action for the manager — never generic advice.

